        <h2>Ducati to Launch 8 New Motorcycles in 2024</h2>
        
        <img src="image/NewsAndArticles/ducati1.jpg" alt="Ducati" class="img-fluid">
        <p><strong>Exciting Announcements:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Hypermotard 698 Mono India Debut</li>
            <li>New Streetfighter V4 Models Incoming</li>
            <li>Limited-edition Panigale V4 Models Confirmed</li>
        </ul>
        <hr>
        
        <p>Ducati India has thrilled its fans with the announcement of launching eight new motorcycles in 2024. In addition to the new models, the brand plans to expand its dealership reach with two more stores in the country.</p>
        <img src="image/NewsAndArticles/ducati2.jpg" alt="Ducati" class="img-fluid">
        
        <p>In the adventure touring segment, Ducati introduces the off-road-focused Rally edition of the DesertX and the RS iteration of the Multistrada V4. The Multistrada V4 RS boasts top-tier components like forged Marchesini wheels, fully adjustable Ohlins suspension, and Brembo Stylema brake calipers. Ducati also surprises enthusiasts with the Hypermotard 698 Mono, the brand's first single-cylinder road-going Hypermotard.</p>
        <img src="image/NewsAndArticles/ducati3.jpg" alt="Ducati" class="img-fluid">
        
        <p>The high-performance sportbike space sees the introduction of the Panigale V4 Racing Replica 2023 and the Panigale V4 SP2 30th Anniversario 916 edition. The latter, an ultra-exclusive offering, pays homage to the 1999 Superbike World Championship-winning Ducati 996. Naked bike enthusiasts can anticipate the new Streetfighter V4S and the Monster 30th Anniversario. Lastly, the Diavel for Bentley, inspired by Bentleyâ€™s Bantur, will grace our shores.</p>
        <img src="image/NewsAndArticles/ducati4.jpg" alt="Ducati" class="img-fluid">
        
        <p>Ducati's 2024 journey begins with the launch of the Streetfighter V4 Lamborghini in the first quarter, followed by the DesertX Rally, Hypermotard 698 Mono, and the new Streetfighter V4 range in Q2. The Multistrada V4 RS and the Diavel for Bentley will make their India entry in Q4 in limited numbers. Official bookings for these motorcycles are already open at all Ducati dealerships.</p>
    
